text: Eyraud-Crempse-Maurens is a commune in the Dordogne department in Aquitaine in southwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Maurens (the seat), Laveyssière, Saint-Jean-d'Eyraud and Saint-Julien-de-Crempse.Arrêté préfectoral 21 September 2018, p. 43 ==See also== *Communes of the Dordogne department ==References== Category:Communes of Dordogne
title: Eyraud-Crempse-Maurens
